## Reviewer Success Hints

**Issue Scope:**
- Issue MUST be within scope of the codebase - a real engineering problem, not made up
- Adding a class/feature that makes no sense in the codebase context will be rejected
- Feature must align with the library's philosophy and intended purpose

**Description Quality:**
- Must be concise with no implementation-specific details (no "how to do")
- API contract details ARE allowed (e.g., "add parameter X that accepts Y")
- NO approach should be prescribed - let solvers design their own implementation

**Test Quality:**
- Tests MUST have relevant edge cases, not just happy paths
- NO hidden requirements - everything tested MUST be documented in README
- If you test it, you MUST tell solvers about it in the problem description

**Problem-Test Alignment (STRICT):**
- ALL behaviors asserted in tests MUST be explicitly stated in the problem description
- The problem MUST align with the tests with NO ambiguity
- This requirement has become stricter in recent updates - reviewers will reject misalignment

