- [ ] README reads like a **REAL ISSUE TICKET**, not API documentation
- [ ] README starts with **USER PROBLEM** (what can't users do today?)
- [ ] README is **3-7 lines** (excluding repo/commit/title header)
- [ ] README describes **CAPABILITIES**, not function signatures
- [ ] README has behavioral requirements with complexity hints where needed
- [ ] README has **NO ambiguity** - all test requirements documented
- [ ] README has **NO implementation hints** (no property names, types, signatures)
- [ ] README has **NO section headers** - flows as continuous prose
- [ ] README **ONLY states tested behaviors** - no extra claims
